    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated for construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). The study confirmed that the production mesh (medium-fine) achieves discretization error below 2% relative to the extrapolated solution, satisfying the acceptance criterion for discretization factor Gradation 3.",
